#Text=Hold a Dog and Tickle Its Toes
#Text=When owning a pupper and having the urge to tickle it , you want to do it properly so that your doggo does n't give you strange looks or misunderstand your intentions .
#Text=If your doge is n't ready for this kind of intimacy you might consider talking about it with them or waiting until your relationship is ready for it .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Lappy tappy
#Text=To do the Lappy Tappy , you must first get the doggo into your lap .
#Text=If your dog is smaller this step is easier to do because you can usually just pick it up .
#Text=However , If your dog is bigger you might have to lure your dog .
#Text=Here are some ways to get the dog into position :
#Text=Treats !
#Text=Find treats that your dog enjoys and tempt them by teasing or leaving a trail to your lap .
#Text=Words of endearment .
#Text=Your dog probably loves you , but if they do n't you might try just using a tone of voice that is non-threatening and saying something like , " Here puppy . " Or " Come here precious . "

column1: #Text=If all else fails you might just have to grab the doggo and carry it to the designated spot .
#Text=Be careful when doing this because some doggies do not like to be picked up or manhandled .
#Text=Getting into position .
#Text=Getting the pupper into position is the harder part .
#Text=You need the doge to be on it 's back if possible to give you access to the little foot fingers that you wish to tickle .
#Text=Try belly rubs .
#Text=Belly rubs are a good way to get the dog to roll over in your lap .
#Text=If your dog is too big for that you might want to try tickling its toes while it 's in sitting position .
#Text=Pats .
#Text=Patting your dog starting at the chest might encourage your doggo to relax or lay down .
#Text=If your dog lays down , it might be the perfect time to tickle .
#Text=Head pets .
#Text=Head pets may relax the pupper and again make it easier to get the dog more comfortable with the idea of tickles on the feets .
#Text=Tickles !
#Text=Once your dog is in position , you can begin the procedure .
#Text=Make sure your dogger is relaxed and is n't trying to escape you .
#Text=You do n't want the pupper in question to misunderstand or feel concerned when you tickle its toes .
#Text=Hyped strike
#Text=If your pupper is a hyper one , you might try the Hyped strike method .
#Text=To begin you must get your doggo excited .
#Text=Grab a toy and tease your doge .
#Text=Some pups only require toys to get them excited .
#Text=Make sure you playfully tease them and wink a lot .
#Text=Ask if your dog would like an adventure .
#Text=Teasing your doggo with an adventure such as going outside can quickly make any lethargic doge into a hyped one .
#Text=Try running around .
#Text=If your house is large enough you might try running around and chasing your pupper until he/she is excited enough for the tickles .
#Text=Talk to them !
#Text=Once your dog is excited and running around you should start calling their name and then running away just to be sure your dog is ready to come for tickles .
#Text=Tickles !
#Text=Now you have to catch your excited dog .
#Text=Chase them around until you manage to catch them .
#Text=Once you have the dog in your possession you can grab the foots and tickle the toes .
#Text=Romantic rubs
#Text=Every pupper loves to be pet or scratched in certain places .
#Text=For a more relaxed toe tickle , you might just try messaging the paws .
#Text=This may also get your doggo accustomed to the feeling of their paws being touched before you proceed to tickle .
#Text=Tickle ' zem .
#Text=Now that your puppo has gotten a desirable message you can proceed to tickle the toes .
#Text=Tickling the foot
#Text=fingers
#Text=If you are unsure of how to properly tickle a doggos toeses , then you need to learn .
#Text=You do n't want your dog to think of you as a weirdo or some kind of creep .
#Text=Take the paws in hand .
#Text=Make sure you have the paw in position by holding it in the palm of your hand .
#Text=Begin to rub in a vertical fashion .
#Text=Move the designated tickle finger up and down on your pup 's paw .
#Text=Rotate .
#Text=Now you may begin moving your finger(s) around the entire bottom of the paw .
#Text=You can go between the toes and even poke at the dog 's toenails .
#Text=Make sure your dog is comfortable with the situation .
#Text=If your pup is giving you strange looks you might want to stop .
#Text=Tips
#Text=Build trust with the dog by asking it personal questions and getting to know it 's preferences .
#Text=Warnings
#Text=Make sure your doggo , pupper , or doge is comfortable in the situation .
